{{reverse_video}}{{bold}} tpg.now {{endbold}}{{endreverse_video}}
tpg.now is an app that shows live data for the Geneva Public Transport system.
(the data is provided by TPG itself, the correctness lies in their hands)


{{reverse_video}}Usage:{{endreverse_video}}
Add filters and choices separated by slashes ('/')
e.g. {{url}}/arg1/arg2/arg3


{{reverse_video}}Arguments:{{endreverse_video}}
/[stop]             enter ONE stop name or code for which you want the departures
                    find stop names and codes on {{url}}/info/stops
                    e.g. {{url}}/Cornavin or {{url}}/AERO
/[stop]/[line]      optionally add one or more line codes to filter
                    e.g. {{url}}/CERN/18/Y to filter lines 18 and Y
/compact            switches to compact output format
/times              displays the departure times, rather than waiting time

/info               get info about the lines and stops operated today
/info/stops         same as /info but only displays stop information
/info/lines         same as /info but only displays line information

/help               display this message


{{reverse_video}}Hint:{{endreverse_video}}
Try using it from CLI with curl
